Market Segmentation (by Application)

Living Room: Polished bricks are increasingly used for accent walls and fireplaces, adding a touch of luxury to interiors.
Kitchen: Durable and easy-to-clean polished bricks are ideal for backsplashes and flooring.
Bathroom: Preferred for their resistance to moisture and aesthetic appeal.
Other: Includes outdoor patios, walkways, and decorative applications.
Market Segmentation (by Type)

Seepage Polished Brick: Engineered to resist water seepage, ideal for areas prone to moisture.
Micro-Powder Polished Brick: Offers a smooth finish and fine texture, popular in luxury designs.
Multi-Tube Cloth Polished Brick: Features intricate patterns, catering to bespoke architectural needs.
Ceramic Stone Polished Brick: Combines the strength of ceramics with the aesthetics of natural stone.
